<TITLE> Fire kills up to 1,600 pigs near Korea border </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Seoul, Dec 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Up to 1,600 pigs were killed in a fire on Sunday at a South Korean farm near the border with North Korea, a fire official said. A glitch in the heating system is blamed for the pre-dawn blaze about 15 km (9 miles) from the border in the Cheorwon county of the northern Gangwon province, the official said by telephone based on a preliminary survey
